```suggestion
    opts = opts and { encoding = 'utf-16' } or { encoding = 'utf-32' }
```

```suggestion
---@param opts? boolean|nil| { encoding: "utf-8"|"utf-16"|"utf-32", error?: boolean }
```

this could be renamed to:

    lua_setfield(lstate, -2, "__str_byteindex");

and then the `vim.str_byteindex` that you defined in `runtime/lua/vim/_editor.lua` can call into this.

